briefdescription.para: Constructor for QgsLayoutItemTextTable, for the specified layout.

detaileddescription.para: Ownership is transferred to the layout.

briefdescription.para: Adds a row to the table.

parameterdescription.para: list of strings to use for each cell's value in the newly added row

simplesect.para: If row is shorter than the number of columns in the table than blank cells will be inserted at the end of the row. If row contains more strings then the number of columns in the table then these extra strings will be ignored.
if adding many rows, setContents() is much faster

briefdescription.para: Fetches the contents used for the cells in the table.

simplesect.para: true if table contents were successfully retrieved.

parameterdescription.para: QgsLayoutTableContents to store retrieved row data in

briefdescription.para: Sets the contents of the text table.
Returns a new QgsLayoutItemTextTable for the specified parent layout.
A text table item that reads text from string lists.
